posts.raw_content: Hey guys, I’ve been thinking about this a lot lately and I just gotta vent. Trump is getting absolutely played by the deep state on immigration, and it’s infuriating to watch.Remember how Biden set up those “humanitarian parole” flights—CHNV and all the other programs? They literally flew hundreds of thousands (maybe millions when you add everything up) of migrants straight into the interior of the country. These people never touched the border, never got hit with expedited removal (you know, the rule that lets ICE boot people caught within 100 miles of the border in the first couple weeks). Nope—just hop on a plane from Caracas or Port-au-Prince, land in Miami or Newark or wherever, get handed parole and work permits, and disappear into cities all over the country. No real oversight, no congressional approval, just executive fiat. Thousands a day at the peak, all on the taxpayer dime.Fast forward to now. Trump’s back in office, promising the biggest deportation operation in history, and what happens? He can’t even get the worst of the worst—the ones with final deportation orders and serious criminal records—out of the country without jumping through a million hoops. Sanctuary cities won’t cooperate, judges are slow-walking cases, and a ton of these Biden parole people are still here because revoking parole en masse takes forever and gets tied up in court. Meanwhile the guys with rape or murder convictions who’ve been ordered removed for years are still walking the streets because “due process” or whatever excuse the bureaucracy comes up with this week.It’s the same playbook they used last time: flood the zone under one administration, then make it practically impossible to reverse under the next. The deep state (career bureaucrats, activist judges, NGO lawyers) built this whole parallel immigration system that bypasses every law Congress ever passed, and now they’re running out the clock on Trump again.Anyone else seeing this? Feels like no matter who we vote for, the permanent government gets its way on open borders.
